up%2017%25%20in%20a%20month.%20Those%20gains%20are%20followed%20by%20a%206%25%20increase%20in%20energy%20and%20a%204%25%20increase%20in%20consumer%20staples%2C%20two%20areas%20that%20are%20thought%20to%20benefit%20from%20higher%20inflation%20and%20the%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foil-prices-outlook-supply-hoarding-iran-war-energy-crisis-2026-04%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoil%20price%20spike%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20materials%2C%20financials%2C%20consumer%20discretionary%2C%20and%20communication%20services%20were%20among%20the%20market's%20biggest%20losers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Berezin%2C%20the%20chief%20global%20strategist%20at%20BCA%20Research%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20divide%20between%20the%20market's%20underperformers%20and%20overperformers%20was%20largely%20due%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bperfect%20storm%26quot%3B%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-inflation-spike-peak-morgan-stanley-gas-prices-economy-oil-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einflationary%20pressures%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%2C%20investors%20are%20weighing%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20latest%20oil%20price%20shock%2C%20which%20could%20feed%20price%20growth%20in%20other%20areas%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20though%20AI%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20disinflationary%20over%20time%2C%20hype%20for%20the%20technology%20is%20currently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-inflation-economy-consumer-cost-energy-price-hike-goldman-sachs-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estoking%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Berezin%20said.%20He%20pointed%20to%20prices%20for%20semiconductors%2C%20chips%2C%20and%20other%20data%20center%20components%2C%20which%20have%20risen%20alongside%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20investors%20have%20lingering%20uncertainty%20regarding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-nominee-kevin-warsh-confirmation-hearing-takeaways-ai-fomc-independence-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKevin%20Warsh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Fed%20Chair%20appointed%20by%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20confirmed%20by%20lawmakers%20last%20week.%20While%20he's%20been%20more%20hawkish%20in%20some%20regards%20than%20markets%20expected%2C%20there's%20still%20some%20concern%20that%20Warsh%20could%20lower%20rates%20prematurely.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20all%20these%20three%20things%20are%20coming%20together%20at%20a%20time%20when%20inflation%20was%20running%20above%20target%20even%20before%202026%2C%26quot%3B%20Berezin%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20how%20pain%20was%20concentrated%20in%20key%20corners%20of%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterials.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHotter%20inflation%20is%20raising%20costs%20for%20many%20materials%20firms%2C%20which%20is%20causing%20investors%20to%20downgrade%20those%20stocks%2C%20Berezin%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFinancials.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20sector%2C%20which%20is%20sensitive%20to%20rates%2C%20is%20indirectly%20impacted%20by%20inflation%20concerns%2C%20Berezin%20added.%20Hotter%20inflation%20could%20lead%20to%20higher%20rates%20in%20the%20long-run%2C%20which%20could%20hit%20lending%20and%20spur%20higher%20defaults%20and%20delinquency%20rates%20among%20businesses%20and%20consumers%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsumer%20discretionary.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EConsumer-facing%20stocks%20will%20likely%20bear%20most%20of%20the%20market's%20pain%20for%20inflation.%20Berezin%20referred%20to%20the%20possibility%20that%20higher%20prices%20could%20cause%20consumers%20to%20pull%20back%20on%20spending%2C%20hurting%20businesses.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ECommunication%20services.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20sector%20is%20in%20decline%20due%20to%20its%20exposure%20to%20consumers%2C%20Berezin%20said.%20He%20pointed%20to%20how%20some%20users%20may%20cancel%20subscriptions%20to%20streaming%20services%20as%20one%20example%20of%20how%20communications%20firms%20could%20be%20affected.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225c4a5bc1-0a1c-4c2f-a517-d5fde5d5e3c1%5C%22%3EThe%20winners%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FY8XOl%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20performance%20of%20the%20S%26amp%3Bamp%3BP%20500's%20technology%20sector%20and%20the%20iShares%20Semiconductor%20ETF%20over%20the%20past%20month%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22461%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEnergy%20%26amp%3B%20consumer%20staples%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EInflation%20hasn't%20been%20as%20much%20of%20a%20headwind%20for%20these%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20outlook%20has%20brightened%20for%20energy%20firms%20alongside%20the%20spike%20in%20oil%20prices%2C%20making%20the%20firm%20a%20beneficiary%20of%20recent%20inflationary%20pressures.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EInflation%20can%20also%20be%20a%20bullish%20factor%20for%20some%20consumer%20staples%20companies%2C%20as%20higher%20prices%20can%20boost%20corporate%20profits%2C%20Jos%C3%A9%20Torres%2C%20a%20senior%20economist%20at%20Interactive%20Brokers%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ETechnology.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EStrong%20earnings%20and%20a%20slew%20of%20dealmaking%20have%20powered%20the%20tech%20sector%20higher.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Fishares-semiconductor-etf-us4642875235%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EiShares%20Semiconductor%20ETF%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20particularly%20salient%20area%20of%20the%20market%20amid%20the%20AI%20boom%2C%20is%20up%2019%25%20over%20the%20past%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20divide%20has%20led%20to%20a%20mixed%20outlook%20for%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20note%20to%20clients%20on%20Monday%2C%20BCA%20Research%20said%20it%20believed%20the%20US%20economy%20looked%20like%20it%20was%20exiting%20the%20%26quot%3Bslowdown%26quot%3B%20phase%20and%20entering%20a%20new%20%26quot%3Bexpansion%26quot%3B%20phase.%20The%20research%20firm%20pointed%20to%20both%20strong%20revenue%2C%20earnings%2C%20and%20capex%20growth%2C%20which%20have%20fueled%20most%20of%20the%20gains%20in%20the%20tech%20sector%2C%20but%20also%20flagged%20the%20risk%20that%20inflation%20concerns%20could%20%26quot%3Bintensify.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrategists%20on%20JPMorgan's%20market%20intelligence%20team%20said%20they%20are%20still%20bullish%20on%20stocks%20overall%2C%20but%20with%20%26quot%3Breduced%20conviction%2C%26quot%3B%20pointing%20to%20how%20inflation%20concerns%20recently%20sparked%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbond-yields-treasury-bonds-stock-market-today-oil-prices-inflation-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehistoric%20sell-off%20in%20bonds%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBond%20vol%20is%20anathema%20for%20stocks%20and%20we%20are%20seeing%20it%20real-time%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bank%20said%20in%20a%20note.%20%26quot%3BWe%20remain%20Tactically%20Bullish%2C%20but%20we%20would%20not%20maximally%20net%20long%20given%20the%20elevated%20probability%20of%20a%20pullback%20led%20by%20Tech.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERate-sensitive%20and%20cyclical%20areas%20of%20the%20market%20will%20likely%20continue%20to%20struggle%2C%20Torres%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20areas%20have%20been%20essentially%20blocked%20from%20achieving%20further%20upside%20because%20they%20can't%20really%20run%20much%20higher%20when%20you%20have%20rates%20this%20elevated%20and%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20really%2C%20investors%20have%20been%20insulating%20themselves%20with%20tech%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchip-semiconductor-stock-gains-spread-beyond-nvidia-cpu-memory-sandisk-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esemiconductors%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETorres%20added%20that%20he%20believed%20the%20split%20between%20stocks%20looked%20unsustainable%2C%20and%20with%20the%20market's%20best%20performers%20likely%20encountering%20future%20challenges%20unless%20rates%20were%20to%20come%20down%20or%20if%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20were%20to%20reopen%2C%20which%20would%20cool%20down%20oil%20prices.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20expect%20that%20rates%20are%20a%20huge%20sentiment%20reverser%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20speculating%20that%20a%20correction%20is%20possible%20in%20the%20near%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-hot-inflation-sp500-winners-losers-tech-stocks-outlook-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1779181801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0b2980ecd7cc1332bb0b14%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-hot-inflation-sp500-winners-losers-tech-stocks-outlook-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stocks%20are%20being%20shuffled%20into%20groups%20of%20winners%20and%20losers%20amid%20the%20resurgence%20of%20inflation%20fears%2C%20optimism%20for%20AI%2C%20and%20predictions%20for%20a%20hot%20economy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jsor%40businessinsider.com%20(Jennifer%20Sor)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20thought%20I%20could%20juggle%20motherhood%20and%20a%20promotion%20at%20Amazon.%20A%20turning%20point%20made%20me%20reevaluate%20everything.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Becca%20Selah%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0bc18d94eb4c909fb2db71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBecca%20Selah%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBecca%20Selah%20took%20a%20job%20as%20a%20senior%20UX%20designer%20at%20Amazon%20months%20after%20having%20a%20baby.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAsked%20to%20lead%20a%20major%20project%2C%20she%20was%20determined%20not%20to%20let%20being%20a%20new%20mom%20define%20her%20at%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20as%20the%20pandemic%20began%20and%20she%20reevaluated%20her%20career%2C%20she%20quit%20her%20job.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-amazon-bar-raiser-tips-to-land-offer-inclined-hire-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einterviewed%20at%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20still%20on%20maternity%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20feeling%20prepared%20but%20nervous%20about%20the%20whiteboard%20exercise.%20I%20worried%20that%20when%20I%20stood%20up%20to%20draw%20boxes%20and%20arrows%2C%20my%20shirt%20might%20ride%20up%20and%20expose%20the%20elastic%20waistband%20of%20my%20maternity%20pants%2C%20revealing%20how%20recently%20I'd%20had%20a%20baby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-got-job-amazon-halo-product-manager-personal-trainer-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejoined%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20senior%20user%20experience%20designer%20in%20April%202019%2C%20my%20daughter%20was%205%20months%20old%2C%20though%20I%20sometimes%20padded%20her%20age%20to%20colleagues%20to%20make%20her%20seem%20less%20like%20a%20liability.%20I%20dropped%20her%20off%20at%20day%20care%20on%20my%20way%20to%20the%20Seattle%20office%2C%20determined%20not%20to%20let%20being%20a%20new%20mom%20define%20how%20people%20saw%20me%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%2030%2C%20and%20I'd%20been%20in%20tech%20long%20enough%20to%20know%20motherhood%20could%20count%20against%20you%20if%20you%20let%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224423419e-4205-4154-94ad-8e6aadf6d771%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20a%20while%2C%20I%20thought%20I%20had%20it%20all%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20start%2C%20I%20kept%20photos%20off%20my%20desk.%20I%20avoided%20mentioning%20daycare%20logistics%2C%20pediatrician%20appointments%2C%20or%20the%20low-grade%20panic%20of%20being%20responsible%20for%20a%20very%20small%20person%20while%20trying%20to%20appear%20fully%20available%20to%20everything%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20boss%20onboarded%20me%20slowly%2C%20and%20for%20a%20while%2C%20I%20thought%20I%20had%20it%20all%3A%20a%20prestigious%20job%2C%20good%20pay%2C%20and%20the%20elusive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-advice-i-ever-got-about-work-life-balance-came-from-partners-mom-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ework-life%20balance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20months%20in%2C%20I%20was%20asked%20to%20lead%20design%20for%20a%20review%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandy-jassy-shareholder-letter-amazon-workforce-tiny-teams-flat-structure-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAndy%20Jassy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20head%20of%20AWS%20at%20the%20time.%20It%20was%20the%20kind%20of%20project%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20promotion%2C%20my%20boss%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hadn't%20been%20thinking%20about%20promotion.%20My%20husband%2C%20who%20also%20worked%20at%20Amazon%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%2C%20said%20it%20could%20take%20years%2C%20if%20it%20happened%20at%20all.%20I%20took%20his%20word%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20new%20to%20Big%20Tech%20and%20had%20spent%20most%20of%20my%20career%20in%20startups%2C%20where%20promotions%20often%20felt%20arbitrary.%20I'd%20once%20gotten%20promoted%20only%20after%20putting%20in%20my%20notice%3B%20it%20came%20with%20a%20%2420K%20raise%20and%20more%20stock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20someone%20hands%20you%20a%20blueprint%2C%20it's%20hard%20not%20to%20imagine%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22442010b0-68b1-4dca-912e-2b2cb3995b7c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20job%20grew%20more%20intense%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMeetings%20began%20appearing%20on%20my%20calendar.%20Weekly%20check-ins%20became%20twice%20a%20week.%20Then%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20pitching%20Andy%20on%20a%20new%20product%20that%20would%20require%20dozens%20of%20engineers%20and%20millions%20of%20dollars.%20As%20the%20designer%2C%20I%20was%20responsible%20for%20shaping%20the%20narrative%20and%20preparing%20a%20handout%20that%20walked%20through%20the%20future%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENormally%2C%20my%20designs%20were%20based%20on%20user%20research%2C%20but%20this%20project%20was%20top%20secret%2C%20so%20I%20couldn't%20talk%20to%20anyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20I%20designed%20for%20Andy%20%E2%80%94%20or%20rather%2C%20each%20person's%20version%20of%20him.%20Everyone%20on%20the%20project%20seemed%20to%20have%20an%20Andy%20story.%20The%20way%20people%20spoke%20about%20him%20made%20me%20feel%20like%20he%20was%20a%20minor%20deity%3A%20brilliant%2C%20capricious.%20It%20became%20clear%20that%20we%20needed%20to%20grab%20his%20attention%20immediately%2C%20frame%20the%20product%20in%20terms%20he%20cared%20about%2C%20and%20be%20ready%20for%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20rehearsed%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-product-manager-resume-tips-big-tech-meta-google-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eproject%20manager%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20played%20the%20role%20of%20Andy%2C%20interrupting%20me%20mid-sentence.%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20this%3F%26quot%3B%20he'd%20ask%2C%20tapping%20the%20screen.%20I'd%20start%20to%20explain%2C%20and%20he'd%20cut%20me%20off%20again.%20It%20felt%20less%20like%20a%20design%20review%20than%20endurance%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221bb0faf7-5ce0-4d7a-9f51-021fe274ebf5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhile%20my%20mind%20was%20elsewhere%2C%20my%20daughter%20was%20growing%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20life%20narrowed.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-employees-layoffs-ai-return-to-office-rto-tracking-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecommuted%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20together.%20Some%20days%20I%20didn't%20leave%20the%20building.%20At%205%20p.m.%2C%20we%20rushed%20to%20day-care%20pickup%2C%20popping%20ibuprofen%20on%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20I'd%20be%20reading%20%26quot%3BLittle%20Blue%20Truck%26quot%3B%20to%20my%20daughter%2C%20but%20my%20mind%20was%20elsewhere%2C%20wondering%20if%20Andy%20would%20prefer%20radio%20buttons%20or%20a%20dropdown%20on%20the%20second%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlowly%2C%20I%20outsourced%20my%20life.%20Other%20people%20watched%20our%20daughter.%20Someone%20cleaned%20the%20house.%20Grocery%20and%20meal%20deliveries%20appeared%20on%20the%20porch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20myself%20it%20was%20temporary.%20By%20then%2C%20it%20had%20been%20about%20four%20months%20of%20intensity%2C%20and%20the%20truth%20was%20that%20mostly%2C%20I%20liked%20it.%20I%20felt%20energized%2C%20important%2C%20almost%20chosen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20though%2C%20I%20was%20tired%2C%20and%20it%20was%20getting%20harder%20to%20ignore%20that%20my%20daughter%20was%20growing%20up%20while%20I%20moved%20through%20it%20all%20in%20a%20haze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBath%20time%20was%20the%20only%20thing%20that%20snapped%20me%20out%20of%20it.%20That's%20when%20I%20first%20noticed%20the%20bite%20marks%20on%20my%20daughter's%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20biter%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20day-care%20staff%20told%20us%2C%20careful%20not%20to%20use%20gendered%20pronouns.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20targeting%20the%20little%20ones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20horrified.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20failing%20her.%20I%20imagined%20someone%20else%20trying%20to%20comfort%20her%20while%20I%20sat%20at%20my%20desk.%20I%20met%20with%20the%20head%20of%20the%20day%20care%2C%20who%20told%20me%20they%20were%20trying%20to%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20biter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20these%20biters%20are%20fast%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20as%20if%20that%20was%20comforting.%20I%20cried%20in%20front%20of%20her%2C%20then%20went%20back%20to%20the%20office%20and%20pushed%20it%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20myself%20this%20was%20what%20someone%20at%20the%20next%20level%20would%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222b938300-1194-483f-b5e3-af1afb011750%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20big%20moment%20finally%20arrived%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20day%20of%20the%20meeting%2C%20months%20of%20work%20had%20been%20distilled%20into%20a%20six-page%20document%20and%20a%20supplemental%20handout%20I'd%20obsessed%20over%20for%20weeks.%20I%20arrived%20early%20and%20sat%20behind%20my%20boss'%20boss.%20It%20began%20the%20way%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-bllionaires-efficient-meetings-amazon-microsoft-apple-google-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emeetings%20always%20did%20at%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20in%20silence%2C%20as%20everyone%20read%20the%20document%20we%20were%20still%20editing%20an%20hour%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndy%20knew%20the%20details%20of%20our%20product%20better%20than%20I%20expected.%20He%20pushed%20on%20the%20tradeoffs%20until%20people%20revised%20themselves%20mid-sentence.%20When%20he%20made%20a%20joke%2C%20people%20laughed%20too%20quickly%2C%20too%20loudly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENinety%20minutes%20later%2C%20we%20had%20our%20funding.%20I%20hadn't%20said%20a%20word.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20people%20gathered%20their%20things%2C%20I%20dropped%20my%20handouts%20into%20the%20recycling%20bin%20on%20the%20way%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20all%20accounts%2C%20the%20meeting%20was%20a%20win.%20It%20should%20have%20felt%20like%20a%20peak.%20Instead%2C%20it%20felt%20flat%2C%20like%20I'd%20spent%20months%20sprinting%20toward%20something%20only%20to%20arrive%20at%20the%20starting%20line%20of%20another%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aad3a4b9-2bc1-4cde-885c-9338e6ca2227%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20to%20think%20more%20clearly%20about%20my%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20we%20left%20for%20Maui%20on%20a%20family%20vacation%20we'd%20booked%20months%20before.%20I%20kept%20my%20phone%20inside%20most%20of%20the%20trip%2C%20grateful%20to%20be%20free%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221995%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22woman%20and%20baby%20on%20beach%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0bc944abc4e9d88574b45f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222660%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESelah%20and%20her%20daughter%20walk%20the%20beach%20during%20their%20family%20vacation.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20walked%20the%20beach%20early%2C%20before%20the%20crowds%20and%20the%20sharp%20midday%20sun.%20Our%20daughter%2C%20now%20a%20year%20old%2C%20found%20a%20set%20of%20measuring%20cups%20in%20the%20Airbnb%20kitchen%20and%20spent%20long%20stretches%20absorbed%20in%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20first%20time%20in%20weeks%20that%20my%20mind%20felt%20quiet.%20And%20in%20that%20quiet%2C%20I%20started%20to%20think%20more%20clearly%20about%20my%20career%2C%20about%20how%20much%20space%20work%20had%20taken%20up%2C%20and%20about%20what%2C%20exactly%2C%20I%20was%20getting%20in%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20see%20why%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-employee-coasted-easy-job-felt-guilty-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estayed%20at%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20colonizes%20your%20mind%20and%20pushes%20everything%20else%20to%20the%20edges.%20It%20makes%20you%20feel%20important%2C%20right%20up%20until%20you%20get%20what%20you%20were%20chasing.%20Then%20it%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20much%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20shared%20my%20theory%20with%20my%20husband%2C%20who%20nodded%20knowingly.%20He%20was%20coming%20up%20on%20his%20five-year%20anniversary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20drug%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20picking%20up%20his%20phone%20to%20check%20his%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22af0e6f28-58e7-4f97-b219-25a8292ba2a9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThen%2C%20the%20pandemic%20hit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20weeks%20after%20we%20returned%20to%20Seattle%2C%20COVID%20hit.%20Within%20a%20month%2C%20we%20lost%20our%20childcare%2C%20our%20cleaning%20lady%2C%20and%20the%20careful%20scaffolding%20we'd%20built%20around%20our%20lives.%20My%20boss%20got%20a%20new%20boss%2C%20who%20brought%20in%20her%20old%20team%2C%20and%20the%20project%20that%20had%20been%20framed%20as%20my%20path%20to%20promotion%20was%20quietly%20handed%20to%20someone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20date%20every%20Amazonian%20knows%3A%20their%20next%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-web-services-stock-compensation-monthly-vesting-l7-top-employees-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estock%20vest%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20it%20approaches%2C%20people%20grow%20reflective.%20You%20start%20asking%20yourself%20whether%20you%20can%20do%20it%20for%20another%20vest%2C%20and%20what%20you're%20willing%20to%20trade%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMine%20was%20a%20month%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20watched%20myself%20in%20the%20corner%20of%20the%20video%20screen%2C%20muting%20and%20unmuting%20as%20my%20daughter%20prattled%20just%20off%20camera%2C%20I%20wondered%3A%20Was%20I%20really%20going%20to%20do%20this%20for%20another%20year%3F%20In%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20pandemic%3F%20With%20a%20small%20child%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20felt%20obvious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20and%20two%20days%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-job-search-success-strategy-tech-software-engineering-role-interview-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejoining%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2271328c02-050f-4520-bba3-86a6860afc3f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20worried%20about%20what%20I'd%20say%20if%20people%20asked%20about%20my%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20exit%20was%20unceremonious%3A%20a%20recurring%20meeting%20repurposed%20as%20a%20send-off%2C%20a%20prepaid%20shipping%20box%20sent%20for%20my%20laptop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stayed%20home%20with%20my%20daughter.%20Without%20the%20structure%20of%20meetings%2C%20the%20days%20began%20to%20blur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worried%20about%20what%20I%20would%20say%20if%20someone%20asked%20what%20I%20did%20for%20work.%20I%20decided%20that%20if%20they%20did%2C%20I'd%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20used%20to%20work%20at%20Amazon%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-do-before-quit-job-dont-leave-money-behind-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EI%20quit%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20I%20liked%20how%20it%20sounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20no%20one%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBecca%20Selah%20is%20a%20freelance%20product%20designer%20who%20writes%20about%20design%2C%20tech%2C%20and%20what%20it's%20like%20to%20work%20in%20both%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2F%40beccaselah%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESubstack%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20your%20career%3F%20Contact%20this%20editor%2C%20Debbie%20Strong%2C%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Adstrong%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Edstrong%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ux-designer-big-tech-promotion-motherhood-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1779181741000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0bc1abecd7cc1332bb0ef2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2