3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EZhang%20Peng%3B%20CFOTO%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20nearly%20half%20a%20century%2C%20China%20has%20been%20the%20factory%20floor%20of%20the%20world%2C%20producing%20everything%20from%20iPhones%20to%20cheap%20sweaters.%20While%20the%20stamp%20%26quot%3BMade%20in%20China%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20ubiquitous%20on%20consumer%20products%2C%20the%20companies%20assembling%20the%20goods%20have%20been%20relatively%20obscure.%20Now%2C%20some%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-retail-brands-labubu-luckin-expand-us-open-stores-data-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina's%20hottest%20brands%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Ewant%3C%2Fem%3E%20you%20to%20know%20their%20names.%20They're%20moving%20from%20the%20background%20of%20global%20commerce%20to%20the%20center%20of%20it%2C%20competing%20directly%20for%20consumers%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Europe%2C%20and%20beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20already%20a%20major%20threat%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Nirgunan%20Tiruchelvam%2C%20the%20head%20of%20consumer%20and%20tech%20equity%20at%20Hong%20Kong-based%20investment%20advisory%20firm%20Aletheia%20Capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fujian-province-based%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-ceo-brian-niccol-chinese-competitor-luckin-coffee-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELuckin%20Coffee%20is%20testing%20markets%3C%2Fa%3E%20long%20dominated%20by%20Starbucks%2C%20like%20New%20York%2C%20with%20app-based%20ordering%20and%20innovative%20limited-edition%20flavors%20like%20blood%20orange%20cold%20brew%20in%20America%20and%20pandan%20coconut%20latte%20in%20Southeast%20Asia.%20Fashion%20brands%20like%20Urban%20Revivo%20and%20Songmont%20are%20competing%20with%20global%20mid-end%20brands%20like%20Zara%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fstyle%2Fbest-luxury-crossbody-bags%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPol%C3%A8ne%20by%20offering%3C%2Fa%3E%20lower%20prices.%20Pop%20Mart%20is%20transforming%20from%20a%20toy%20company%20to%20a%20global%20cultural%20force%20via%20their%20tiny%2C%20cute%20collectibles%20%E2%80%94%20most%20notably%20Labubus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20Chinese%20companies%20have%20tried%20to%20remake%20the%20global%20business%20landscape.%20In%20the%202000s%2C%20Beijing%20pushed%20some%20of%20its%20less%20sexy%20but%20state-backed%20industrial%20giants%2C%20like%20China%20National%20Petroleum%20Corporation%20and%20China%20Railway%20Construction%20Corp%20to%20%26quot%3Bgo%20out%20%26quot%3Babroad%20to%20secure%20resources%20and%20build%20infrastructure.%20In%20the%202010s%2C%20Chinese%20firms%20went%20on%20a%20global%20buying%20spree%2C%20snapping%20up%20everything%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famc-stock-ownership-cut-by-largest-shareholder-after-record-loss-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAMC%20Theatres%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-chinas-anbang-is-buying-the-waldorf-astoria-2014-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWaldorf%20Astoria.%3C%2Fa%3E%20More%20recently%2C%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbyd-sales-surpass-tesla-china-ev-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectric%20vehicle%20maker%20BYD%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20drone%20maker%20DJI%20proved%20that%20Chinese%20firms%20could%20compete%20globally%20by%20providing%20cutting-edge%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20lower%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20vanguard%20of%20Chinese%20brands%20heading%20out%20to%20conquer%20the%20world%20is%20attempting%20something%20harder%20than%20getting%20in%20with%20the%20lowest%20price%20or%20newest%20tech%3A%20being%20cool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bbef8d5c-9fcb-4c29-ad24-88cb9d323d4e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20challenge%20of%20crafting%20an%20identity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20is%20one%20thing%20that%20Chinese%20brands%20are%20known%20for%20around%20the%20world%2C%20it's%20rock-bottom%20prices.%20The%20country's%20best-known%20consumer%20brands%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-companies-cracked-code-on-getting-people-hooked-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShein%20and%20Temu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20gained%20a%20following%20for%20their%20lightning-fast%20delivery%20times%20and%20low%20cost.%20Despite%20tariffs%2C%20privately%20held%20Shein%20was%20expected%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2025-11-06%2Fshein-eyes-2-billion-profit-in-2025-despite-us-tariff-headwinds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edouble%20its%20profits%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0last%20year%2C%20while%20revenue%20for%20Temu%20parent%20PDD%20Holdings%20grew%2010%25%20%E2%80%94%20though%20profits%20fell%2012%25%20%E2%80%94%20over%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20Chinese%20brands%20trying%20to%20make%20the%20leap%20abroad%20have%20similarly%20gained%20attention%20for%20their%20value.%20Nowhere%20is%20this%20clearer%20than%20on%20social%20media%2C%20where%20users%20post%20unboxings%20of%20their%20Songmont%20bags%2C%20%241.99%20Luckin%20beverages%2C%20and%20%241.19%20Mixue%20ice%20cream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20price%2C%20honestly%20not%20bad%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jon%20Barr%2C%20a%20New%20York%20City%20TikToker%20with%20105%2C000%20followers%2C%20after%20trying%20a%20%243.99%20Taro%20milk%20tea%20and%20a%20%241.19%20soft%20serve%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-biggest-fast-food-chain-mixue-china-bubble-tea-ipo-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efast-food%20chain%20Mixue%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20said%20beat%20McDonald's.%20He%20said%20he%20would%20be%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurning%20homemade%20brands%20into%20global%20cultural%20powers%20is%20also%20a%20survival%20tactic.%20China%20remains%20mired%20in%20a%20drawn-out%20economic%20slowdown%2C%20and%20its%20birthrate%20tumbled%20to%20a%20record%20low%20in%202025.%20China's%20consumer%20market%2C%20once%20a%20seemingly%20endless%20engine%20of%20growth%2C%20has%20become%20crowded%20and%20unforgiving.%20Relentless%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-aggressive-price-cutting-unhealthy-competition-involution-economy-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Binvolutionary%26quot%3B%20price%20wars%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20eroding%20margins%20at%20home.%20Looking%20abroad%20is%20necessary%20if%20these%20companies%20want%20to%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20these%20companies%20are%20set%20up%20for%20success%20from%20an%20operations%20standpoint%3A%20Years%20of%20surviving%20one%20of%20the%20most%20competitive%20markets%20in%20the%20world%20have%20made%20them%20experts%20in%20manufacturing%2C%20sales%2C%20and%20scaling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%20is%20transforming%20itself%20from%20a%20low-priced%20manufacturer%20into%20a%20producer%20of%20brands%20with%20unique%20personalities%20and%20storylines%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Eunkyu%20Lee%2C%20a%20marketing%20professor%20at%20Syracuse%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20whether%20they%20can%20become%20household%20names%20in%20categories%20where%20brand%2C%20identity%2C%20and%20perception%20matter%20is%20a%20different%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENational%20identities%20can%20help%20to%20turn%20mere%20merchandise%20into%20objects%20of%20meaning%20and%20desire%2C%20building%20geopolitical%20influence%20through%20commercial%20means.%20European%20houses%20have%20long%20hung%20their%20identities%20on%20heritage%2C%20craftsmanship%2C%20and%20luxury%2C%20while%20American%20brands%20export%20innovation%2C%20freedom%2C%20and%20optimism.%20Some%20of%20China's%20neighbors%20have%20developed%20a%20national%20brand%20more%20recently.%20From%20the%201960s%20to%20the%202000s%2C%20Japan%20and%20South%20Korea%20moved%20from%20low-cost%20manufacturing%20to%20brand-led%20competition%2C%20%C3%A0%20la%20Sony%2C%20Samsung%2C%20Nintendo%2C%20and%20Uniqlo.%20Japanese%20brands%20became%20synonymous%20with%20minimalism%20and%20precision.%20South%20Korean%20brands%20rode%20a%20wave%20of%20trend-driven%20pop%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20now%20trying%20to%20do%20the%20same%2C%20but%20at%20a%20faster%20pace%20and%20without%20a%20clear%20answer%20yet%20to%20what%20the%20defining%20identity%20is.%20That%20matters%20because%20identity%20is%20what%20allows%20brands%20to%20move%20from%20being%20chosen%20for%20price%20to%20being%20chosen%20for%20passion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22428e7057-88d4-4a04-a05f-b99420e42adf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWinning%20over%20global%20culture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20Chinese%20companies%20appear%20to%20be%20taking%20two%20distinct%20approaches%20toward%20globalizing%20their%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20some%20companies%20are%20trying%20to%20soften%20or%20minimize%20their%20Chinese%20identity.%20Some%20of%20China's%20biggest%20global%20consumer%20successes%2C%20from%20Shein%20to%20TikTok%2C%20became%20internationally%20popular%20not%20by%20emphasizing%20their%20origins%2C%20but%20by%20presenting%20themselves%20as%20internet-native%20global%20platforms.%20That%20strategy%20works%20especially%20well%20in%20an%20online%20culture%20where%20hype%20travels%20faster%20than%20provenance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20younger%20consumers%2C%20the%20search%20for%20the%20new%20is%20constant.%20Brand%20discovery%20happens%20on%20TikTok%2C%20Instagram%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frednote-fast-becoming-regular-american-window-into-china-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERedNote%20(named%20Xiaohongshu%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20China)%2C%20and%20other%20platforms.%20In%20that%20environment%2C%20it%20doesn't%20matter%20where%20the%20product%20is%20from%2C%20as%20long%20as%20it's%20hot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20looking%20for%20something%20that%20is%20new%2C%20cool%2C%20and%20fresh%2C%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ELee%2C%20the%20Syracuse%20professor%2C%20says.%20In%20that%20context%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20country%20of%20origin%20is%20not%20very%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESportswear%20brand%20Li-Ning%20has%20gained%20visibility%20by%20sponsoring%20NBA%20players%20like%20Jimmy%20Butler%20and%20CJ%20McCollum%2C%20bringing%20Chinese-designed%20sneakers%20onto%20a%20global%20stage.%20That%20kind%20of%20cultural%20crossover%20is%20how%20brands%20begin%20to%20matter.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Pop%20Mart%20has%20collaborated%20with%20Disney%20and%20Sanrio's%20Hello%20Kitty%2C%20placing%20its%20characters%20alongside%20some%20of%20the%20most%20recognizable%20names%20in%20global%20pop%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWinning%20attention%20is%20one%20thing%20%E2%80%94%20sustaining%20it%20is%20another.%20Many%20Chinese%20brands%20still%20rely%20on%20a%20familiar%20formula%3A%20good%20design%2C%20acceptable%20quality%2C%20lower%20price.%20That%20is%20enough%20to%20attract%20customers.%20It%20is%20not%20always%20enough%20to%20keep%20them.%20Even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpop-mart-stock-plummeting-labubu-reliance-earnings-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPop%20Mart%20shares%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20already%2020%25%20lower%20this%20year%20amid%20fears%20it%20could%20be%20a%20one-trick%20pony%20built%20on%20Labubu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20danger%20is%20if%20you%20try%20to%20take%20on%20these%20Western%20brands%20with%20a%20me-too%20approach%20instead%20of%20coming%20up%20with%20your%20own%20answers%2C%26quot%3B%20Aletheia%20Capital's%20Tiruchelvam%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223150%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22labubu%20popmart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a04792b58810e27922ad211%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPop%20Mart's%20Labubus%20have%20broken%20into%20US%20culture%2C%20even%20iconic%20American%20events%20like%20the%20Thanksgiving%20Day%20parade%3Cp%3EMichael%20Simon%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20POP%20MART%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20other%20brands%20%E2%80%94%20Songmont%2C%20Laopu%2C%20and%20the%20tea%20chain%20Chagee%20%E2%80%94%20are%20doubling%20down%20on%20Chinese%20aesthetics%2C%20heritage%2C%20and%20ritual.%20A%20growing%20wave%20of%20online%20fascination%20with%20Chinese%20lifestyle%20and%20aesthetics%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinamaxxing-tiktok-chinese-habits-wellness-hot-water-boiled-apples-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edubbed%20%26quot%3BChina-maxxing%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20suggests%20global%20consumers%20may%20be%20more%20open%20than%20before%20to%20brands%20that%20foreground%2C%20rather%20than%20soften%2C%20their%20origins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20signs%20that%20global%20players%20are%20starting%20to%20take%20notice.%20Songmont%2C%20an%20affordable%20luxury%20bag%20brand%20whose%20minimalist%20leather%20bags%20top%20out%20at%20around%20%24800%2C%20draws%20inspiration%20from%20Chinese%20roots%2C%20with%20designs%20inspired%20by%20the%20roofs%20of%20a%20Buddhist%20temple%20and%20traditional%20kites.%20The%2013-year-old%20brand%20has%20drawn%20the%20attention%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2025-11-16%2Fchina-s-luxury-brands-songmont-laopu-gold-steal-spotlight-from-lvmh-and-gucci%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELVMH%20CEO%20Bernard%20Arnault%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20visited%20a%20Songmont%20shop%20%E2%80%94%20and%20bought%20two%20bags%20%E2%80%94%20during%20a%20September%20visit%20to%20Shanghai.%20During%20his%20trip%2C%20Arnault%20also%20visited%20Laopu%20Gold%20%E2%80%94%20dubbed%20the%20%26quot%3BHermes%20of%20gold%26quot%3B%20in%20China%20%E2%80%94%20a%20jewelry%20shop%20specializing%20in%20handcrafted%2024K%20gold%20pieces%20inspired%20by%20Chinese%20culture%20and%20symbolism%2C%20such%20as%20dragons%20and%20gourds.%20In%20mid-April%2C%20Gucci's%20owner%2C%20Kering%2C%20announced%20that%20it%20would%20acquire%20a%20minority%20stake%20in%20Shanghai%20fashion%20brand%20Icicle%20%E2%80%94%20a%20high-end%20label%20often%20compared%20to%20Max%20Mara.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20approaches%20can%20work%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20an%20online%20culture%20that%20rewards%20what%20feels%20new%2C%20distinctive%2C%20and%20shareable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22756c9d00-76b6-4e58-b045-b6b2ca7f6cb2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitics%20can't%20stop%20personal%20choices%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20another%20issue%20that%20could%20complicate%20Chinese%20brands'%20efforts%20to%20win%20over%20customers%20outside%20their%20home%20country%3A%20politics.%20Trade%20tensions%20have%20reshaped%20supply%20chains%20and%20put%20Chinese%20tech%20companies%2C%20such%20as%20TikTok%2C%20under%20scrutiny.%20BYD%20has%20expanded%20rapidly%20in%20Europe%20and%20South%20America%2C%20but%20is%20still%20locked%20out%20of%20the%20US%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-electric-car-get-ready-to-pay-250-percent-tariff-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprohibitively%20high%20tariffs.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Tariffs%20have%20hit%20companies%20like%20Shein%20and%20Temu%2C%20but%20they%20haven't%20stopped%20them.%20Instead%2C%20these%20companies%20are%20adapting%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftemu-ceasing-direct-chinese-shipments-to-us-de-minimis-tariff-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocalizing%20operations%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20finding%20ways%20to%20stay%20competitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20wave%20of%20Chinese%20companies%20attempting%20to%20crack%20the%20American%20and%20Western%20markets%20is%20better%20positioned%20%E2%80%94%20because%20they%20are%20also%20increasingly%20able%20to%20sell%20products%20as%20desirable%20cultural%20goods%20with%20real%20pricing%20power.%20And%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20policy%20can%20only%20slow%20desire%20for%20so%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernments%20will%20probably%20find%20it%20difficult%20to%20stop%20consumers%20from%20embracing%20Chinese%20brands%2C%20Lee%20says%2C%20in%20part%20because%20%26quot%3Bthese%20brands%20are%20largely%20detached%20from%20political%20issues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20politics%20may%20be%20a%20short-term%20hurdle%2C%20long-term%20success%20will%20depend%20on%20whether%20Chinese%20brands%20can%20cross%20over%20from%20being%20chosen%20because%20they%20are%20cheap%20or%20a%20novelty%20to%20being%20chosen%20because%20they%20are%20desirable%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuccess%20would%20be%20some%20of%20the%20brands%20achieving%20premium%20brand%20recognition%20among%20global%20consumers%20and%20being%20able%20to%20command%20a%20price%20premium%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20will%20take%20time%2C%20but%20the%20direction%20is%20clear%3A%20China%20has%20already%20changed%20how%20the%20world%20makes%20things%20with%20its%20ultra-efficient%20supply%20chains.%20Now%20it%20is%20trying%20to%20compete%20for%20what%20the%20world%20wants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fhuileng-tan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EHuileng%20Tan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20business%20reporter%20based%20in%20Singapore%2C%20covering%20markets%2C%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20commodities.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-brands-luckin-popmart-starbucks-nike-american-consumers-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1779178381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.i