E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222750%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20celebrating%20her%2023rd%20birthday%2C%20the%20year%20she%20started%20grad%20school%2C%20with%20her%20then%203-year-old.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0b3f7594eb4c909fb2d875%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221878%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20celebrating%20her%2023rd%20birthday%2C%20the%20year%20she%20started%20grad%20school%2C%20with%20her%20then%203-year-old.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Trisha%20Daab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20year%2C%20that%20salary%20increased%20to%20around%20%2436%2C000%2C%20but%20I%20was%20eager%20to%20get%20promoted%20and%20make%20even%20more%20money.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EA%20manager%20gave%20me%20some%20advice%3A%20I%20would%20need%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployed-recent-college-grad-applied-thousand-jobs-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emaster's%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20have%20any%20hope%20of%20moving%20up.%20I%20listened%20and%20started%20grad%20school%20in%202003.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245ce42a1-7fcf-45ab-9e0a-98dc67e183c3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20loans%20quickly%20added%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20years%20later%2C%20I%20had%20my%20MBA%20and%20a%20bill%20for%20over%20%2469%2C000.%20This%20was%20the%20combined%20total%20of%20my%20%2420%2C000%20in%20unsubsidized%20undergrad%20and%20over%20%2449%2C000%20subsidized%20grad-school%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22510%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%2C%20after%20her%20grad%20school%20graduation%2C%20with%20her%20husband%20at%20Navy%20Pier%20in%20Chicago.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0b3fda94eb4c909fb2d878%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22383%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20after%20her%20grad%20school%20graduation%2C%20with%20her%20husband%20at%20Navy%20Pier%20in%20Chicago.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Trisha%20Daab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20that%20was%20a%20terrifying%20amount.%20After%20all%2C%20it%20was%20more%20money%20than%20I%20had%20ever%20made%20in%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20manager%20was%20right.%20Getting%20my%20MBA%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-amazon-vp-explains-simplest-way-to-get-promoted-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20key%20to%20getting%20promoted%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20happened%20in%202006%20when%20I%20landed%20a%20new%20job%20with%20a%20better%20title%20at%20a%20new%20company.%20My%20salary%20and%20bonuses%20greatly%20increased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f3335da4-4ce2-4723-87b6-c8655b2e6ad6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20almost%2020%20years%2C%20I%20made%20that%20monthly%20payment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20amount%20of%20my%20payment%20that%20applied%20to%20interest%20varied%20greatly%20over%20the%2020%20years%20it%20took%20to%20repay%20my%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20standard%20consolidated%2030-year%20loan.%20My%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fcurrent-student-loan-interest-rates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efirst%20loan%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20in%20December%20of%202006%2C%20and%20the%20automatic%20payments%20I%20set%20up%20would%20continue%20until%20November%20of%202036.%20Every%20single%20month%2C%20%24345.19%20was%20deducted%20from%20my%20checking%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20two%20payments%20went%20entirely%20toward%20interest%2C%20which%20was%20hard%20to%20stomach.%20Over%20the%20years%20that%20shifted%20to%20about%2050%2F50%20principal%20and%20interest%2C%20and%20then%20the%20interest%20got%20lower%20and%20lower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dfe6d14e-9b88-4789-b085-4286a56708e8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20eventually%20started%20paying%20more%20than%20the%20minimum%20amount%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20oldest%20son%20graduated%20from%20college%20in%202022%2C%20and%20I%20was%20no%20longer%20giving%20him%20money%20for%20school%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20make%20extra%20payments%20and%20put%20a%20portion%20of%20my%20annual%20bonuses%20toward%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-student-loan-debt-repayment-struggle-warning-for-federal-borrowers-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eloan%20repayment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20was%20determined%20not%20to%20be%20paying%20my%20student%20loans%20into%20my%20mid-50s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20paid%20off%20the%20loan%20in%20early%202026.%20Rather%20than%20the%20estimated%20%24108%2C000%2C%20the%20total%20amount%20paid%20was%20%2498%2C442.88.%20It%20worked%20out%20to%20be%20%2469%2C928.46%20in%20principal%20and%20%2428%2C514.52%20in%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b3ea3676-3397-4fe5-8c95-b9aaf1499fcc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20didn't%20realize%20how%20freeing%20it%20would%20be%20to%20pay%20off%20these%20loans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20life%20changed%20enormously%20in%20the%2020%20years%20I%20had%20been%20paying%20off%20my%20student%20loans.%20I%20had%20another%20child.%20I%20got%20promotions%2C%20changed%20companies%2C%20and%20helped%20my%20son%20and%20three%20stepchildren%20get%20through%20college%2C%20all%20while%20paying%20my%20own%20student%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20made%20a%20career%20change%20in%202023%20and%20walked%20away%20from%20marketing%20and%20Corporate%20America%20%E2%80%94%20the%20reason%20I%20had%20gone%20to%20grad%20school%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20But%20every%20monthly%20student%20loan%20payment%20was%20a%20reminder%20of%20the%20investment%20I%20made%20in%20a%20career%20I%20no%20longer%20wanted.%20Some%20days%2C%20I%20felt%20irresponsible%2C%20paying%20for%20this%20degree%20I%20wasn't%20really%20using%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%2C%20two%20major%20life%20changes%20%E2%80%94%20my%20youngest%20graduating%20from%20high%20school%20and%20my%20husband%20retiring%20